OL,3,CSecretary of State: Increase in
OL,4,Cminimum wage will be 'real help'
OL,6,FNorthern Ireland Secretary Hilary Benn
OL,7,Fhas said a rise in the minimum wage
OL,8,Fwill be "a real help" as he insisted
OL,9,Fthose not able to work "will be
OL,10,Fprotected" from the Government's
OL,11,Fbenefit cuts.
OL,13,FEligible full-time workers are set for
OL,14,Fa pay boost of up to #117 from this
OL,15,Fmonth as the Government's increase in
OL,16,Fthe national living wage comes into
OL,17,Feffect.
OL,19,FSpeaking outside Westminster, Mr Benn
OL,20,Fdescribed the change as "a real help
OL,21,Fto people when times are tough".
